            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-12-17T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-12-17T17:00:00-05:00" n="423" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d423">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">701.6474/12–1145: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the United States Representative in Bulgaria</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Barnes</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-12-17T17:00:00-05:00">December 17, 1945—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>405. Dept continues to adhere to view expressed Deptel 20, Jan 25 that it is
                    unnecessary and undesirable for enemy states to have direct diplomatic relations
                    between themselves so long as they remain under armistice regimes. Brit and
                    Soviet Govt expressed agreement this attitude at that time.</p>
                <p>Accordingly, message contained urtel 750, Dec 11<note n="48" xml:id="d423fn1">Not
                        printed; it reported a message regarding proposed renewal of diplomatic
                        relations between Bulgaria and Hungary which a representative of the
                        Hungarian colony in Sofia wished to have communicated to the Hungarian
                        Government (701.6474/12–1145).</note> should not be transmitted to Hungarian
                    Govt.</p>
                <p>Sent to Sofia, rptd to Budapest.<note n="49" xml:id="d423fn2">As No. 835.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
